// A match arm's narrowed scrutinee flows BARE at the arm's type -- as a call argument, not
// just through field reads. Before narrowing was wired end-to-end, the checker rebound `v`
// to `A` in the arm but lowering never converted the value: the bare use fell through
// coercion's dead branch and `takes_a(v)` received a ZEROED `A` -- this program printed 0,
// silently. The fix is the projection at the variable-use funnel (`lower_path` emits the
// cast when the use's repr is narrower than the binding's), which is the same mechanism
// `if`/`while` narrowing rides on (control/narrowing_in_if_and_while.neon).

use std::io;

record A { x: i64 }
record B { y: i64 }

fn takes_a(a: A) -> i64 { a.x }

fn main() {
    let v: A | B = A { x: 42 };
    match v {
        is A => io::println(to_string(takes_a(v))),
        is B => io::println("was B"),
    }
}
